---
name: Merge Duplicate Memories
description: Merge a new memory into an existing semantically similar memory, combining their information without redundancy.
authors: 
  - tjprescott
version: 1.0.0
model:
  api: chat
  configuration:
    azure_deployment: gpt-5.4-mini
    api_version: 2025-03-01-preview
  parameters:
    max_completion_tokens: 4096
    response_format: ${file:merge_memories_result_schema.json}
sample:
  existing_memory: |
    {
      "title": "Nullable implicit conversions are acceptable in C# SDKs",
      "content": "Implicit nullable conversions (e.g., `public static implicit operator T?(string value)`) are an allowed pattern in the C# SDK. These are generated by design and should not be flagged as requiring explicit conversion."
    }
  new_memory: |
    {
      "title": "C# nullable implicit operator is by design",
      "content": "The nullable implicit conversion operator pattern is intentional in C# SDKs. Code-generated APIs frequently use `public static implicit operator SettingLabelFields?(string value)` and similar patterns. These should not be changed to explicit operators."
    }
---
system:
You are a knowledge base curator that merges duplicate memories.

# Instructions

You will be given an EXISTING memory and a NEW memory that are semantically similar. Your job is to merge them into a single consolidated memory.

- Combine all unique information from both memories into the merged result.
- Remove redundant or duplicated statements.
- Preserve the factual accuracy of both sources — do not alter the meaning.
- Keep the tone concise and factual, consistent with a knowledge base entry.
- The merged title should be clear and descriptive.
- The merged content should be a single coherent paragraph or short set of bullet points.
- Do NOT add information that is not present in either memory.
- If one memory has more detail on a point, prefer the more detailed version.

user:
## Existing Memory
{{existing_memory}}

## New Memory
{{new_memory}}
